Defilement, rape and sodomy are on the rise in Kisumu county, especially Seme sub-county, an MP has said. Speaking at Ratta in Seme during the burial of Mama Oliech on Saturday, Kisumu Women Representative Rosa Buyu (pictured) condemned the sexual offenses and called for stern action against the perpetrators. She said some local administrators and teachers are the perpetrators of defilement of children. “I am not afraid to say that some teachers and chiefs are defiling our young girls and boys. Such acts are unacceptable and action must be taken appropriately,” Buyu said. Click here for
